Adventure A: Race for the Crown (Korvanjund)
Villain: Ulag the Breaker (Tank/Tactician - Dragon Cult).
Theme: Warfare. A three-way siege. The Stormcloaks want the Crown for legitimacy; Ulag wants it to demoralize the mortals, to plant fear and doubt that maybe the dragon priests claim is legitimate.
Conflict Type: Assault / Race against Time.
The Narrative Hook:
Galmar Stone-Fist is besieging the ruin. His scouts are dead. He believes it's just Draugr. In reality, Ulag the Breaker has occupied the ruin to retrieve the Jagged Crown. However, Ulag is a soldier, not a priest; he doesn't know the cipher to open the final vault and has been stalled trying to breach it when the Stormcloaks arrived.
The Map Structure:
Section 1 (The Siege Camp - Guardian): The exterior. Galmar's forces are pinned down by Ulag's Deathlord archers. The party must break the suppression fire to meet Galmar.
Section 2 (The Hall of Stories - The Breach): The entrance. Ulag has barricaded the doors. The "Puzzle" is finding a way to breach the defenses while under fire.
Section 3 (The Crypt - The Meat Grinder): MASSIVE SCALE WAR fighting. Ulag's minions (Disciplined Deathlords) use shield walls and tactics.
Section 4 (The Throne Room - The Boss Fight): Ulag is at the puzzle door, frustrated. He fights the party and Galmar simultaneously.
The Escape Condition: If Ulag drops below 25% HP, he realizes the position is lost. He triggers a structural collapse (using his "Break the Wall" technique on a support pillar) to bury the Crown room, denying it to everyone while he escapes through a secret passage.


Section 5 (The Vault): If the party stops the collapse, they solve the puzzle Ulag couldn't and claim the Crown.

