The Revised Structure
Adventure A: Race for the Crown (Full Corrected Outline)
Location: Korvanjund
Context: A joint operation between the Wardens and the Stormcloaks in a massive, active warzone.
Themes: Siege Warfare, Family Drama (Davinia/Galmar), Physics/Engineering (Ulag).
Prologue: The Road & The Wolf
The Journey: Traveling from Kynesgrove to the Pale.
The Encounter: Ylva the Cleaver intercepts the party. She recognizes them from their reputation.
The Interaction: She forcibly joins the group. If resisted, she challenges their strongest (Kyboh) to a non-lethal brawl to prove her worth. She respects their strength.
The Lore: Ylva provides the "Nord Perspective" on the warΓÇöit's about land and freedom, not just politics.
Section 1: The Siege Lines (Social & Combat)
The Setting: The exterior of Korvanjund. A sprawling siege camp. Stormcloaks are pinned down by Dragon Cult fire from the walls.
The Social Tension: Stormcloak soldiers are suspicious of the "Imperial" Wardens. High stakes to avoid hostility.
The Reveal: Galmar Stone-Fist spots Davinia. He recognizes her not just as a Warden, but as "Little Davinia," the daughter of his former friend. He is warm, supportive, and deferential to her tactical judgment, contrasting with her father's rigidity.
The Action: Galmar asks for Davinia's input on how to break the siege. The party executes a plan to silence the enemy artillery so the army can breach the gate.
Section 2: The Hall of Stories (Integrated Dungeon - The Severed Path)
The Setting: A massive, vertical antechamber.
The Logic: Ulag did not lock the door behind him; his rear guard physically raised the bridge to cut off pursuit.
The Puzzle: To proceed, the party must lower the bridge. The mechanism is locked by Counter-Weights located in two side wings (The Armory and The Embalming Hall).
The Gameplay: The party must fight through these active, populated side rooms to release the chains. It forces engagement with the space.
The Atmosphere: Arrows fly across the central chasm. It is a chaotic firefight, not a quiet puzzle.
Section 3: The Crypt (The Meat Grinder)
The Setting: A vast, open cavern filled with coffins and stone bridges. "Mines of Moria" scale.
The Conflict: Open Warfare. Galmar's forces breach the crypt. It is a 20 vs. 50 brawl.
The Party's Role: Special Forces. Galmar holds the line against the horde. The party must push forward to eliminate high-value targets (Draugr Casters/Archers on high ground) and destroy "Spawners" (Sarcophagi) to stop the flow of enemies.
Section 4: The Throne Room (The Standoff)
The Setting: The inner sanctum. Ulag is here, but he isn't waiting on a throne.
The Narrative Hook: Ulag is drilling. He has a massive, alchemical drilling rig set up against the final vault door. He is frustrated because he doesn't know the cipher/key to open it properly.
The Surprise: Ulag is genuinely surprised the party broke through. He expected his rear guard to hold forever.
The Combat: Ulag vs. Galmar + Party.
Galmar's Role: He engages Ulag directly, locking weapons.
Ulag's Sadism: If he downs a player and is above 80% HP, he uses a necromantic ability to revive them with 1 HP just to hit them again. "You do not have permission to die yet."
The Timer: The drill is still running. The party must stop Ulag before he breaches the vault or collapses the room.


Section 5: The Collapse (The Escape)
The Climax: When Ulag drops to critical health (25%), he realizes he can't win. He prioritizes denial.
The Action: He uses his "Break the Wall" technique on a load-bearing pillar to collapse the ceiling on the Vault entrance, intending to bury the Crown. He escapes through a secret passage.
The Resolution: The party must scramble to grab the Crown from the debris and drag wounded allies (Galmar) to safety before the room seals.
The Rewards:
The Jagged Crown.
Boots of the Comet: (For Kyboh).
Galmar's Token: A personal gift for Davinia.


